          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Logic and Programming</strong></p><p>Computational Thinking is a suite of skills that define the ability to break a problem apart and apply math and logic to it so it can be solved efficiently. There are several tools to do this in CLUE, the most obvious of which is a programming tile. These tiles allow you to read sensor data or generate series of numeric inputs, then transform the numbers and use them to control outputs. You don&#x27;t need to know much to get started, except perhaps that 0 = off and 1 = on. Here are a set of program blocks. They make a series of numbers which you can see in the minigraphs.</p>"
          ]
        }
